    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302934">Figure 34</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302934" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302934" filename="../figg13/g1302934.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 34. Auxiliary Countershaft Assemblies</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Place the synchronizer in HI range before removal of the countershafts.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the countershafts forward through the countershaft bearings
                and remove them from the auxiliary housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302935">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302935" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302935" filename="../figg13/g1302935.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Drive Countershafts Forward Through Countershaft Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft bearings from the auxiliary case bearing bores (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302936">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302936" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302936" filename="../figg13/g1302936.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Remove Countershaft Bearings From Auxiliary Case Bearing Bores</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, secure the assembly in a vise and remove the auxiliary countershaft front
                bearing race from the countershaft with a jaw puller and clamp (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302937">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302937" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302937" filename="../figg13/g1302937.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Remove Auxiliary Countershaft Front Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The vise should be equipped with soft jaws or wood blocks to prevent damage to the countershaft.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
